05447nam a22008895i 9781487543198DE-B159720220629043637.0m|||||o||d||||||||cr || ||||||||220629t20222022onc    fo  d z      eng d  a97814875431987 a10.3138/97814875431982doi  a(DE-B1597)618976  a(OCoLC)1286372810  aDE-B1597bengcDE-B1597erda0 aeng  aonccCA-ON 4aHN583.5 7aPOL0100002bisacsh04a306.09462231 aOuziel, Pablo, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut10aDemocracy Here and Now :bThe Exemplary Case of Spain /cPablo Ouziel. 1aToronto : bUniversity of Toronto Press, c[2022] 4c©2022  a1 online resource (216 p.) :b1 b&w map  atextbtxt2rdacontent  acomputerbc2rdamedia  aonline resourcebcr2rdacarrier  atext filebPDF2rda00tFrontmatter -- tContents -- tAcknowledgments -- tForeword -- tVisiting 15M Locales across Spain -- tSix Distinct Types of Joining Hands Relationships -- tIntroduction: Studying Democracies – Learning via Examples and Exemplarity -- t1 Exercising Power Together as Equals -- t2 Roots and Routes of Spain’s Counter-Modernity -- t3 Constructing Alternative Futures on Shoestring Budgets -- t4 Engaging State-Based Representative Government -- tConclusion: Democracy Here and Now -- tBibliography -- tIndex0 arestricted accessuhttp://purl.org/coar/access_right/c_16ecfonline access with authorization2star  aIn Spain, on May 15, 2011, a movement against austerity measures began. In a time when representative democracies were under threat, 15M came to life as a virtuous and democratic response to the slide into far-right populism and authoritarianism. More than a social movement, 15M became a mode of being with transformative, democratizing potential. In Democracy Here and Now, Pablo Ouziel offers a grounded analysis of 15M. At the time of the movement and during the ensuing encampments, Ouziel travelled extensively, speaking to participants, and keeping an ongoing record of his conversations. Presenting an original participatory mode of research, the book reveals six types of intersubjective, "joining hands" relationships that 15M has brought into being and works to carry on in creative ways. The book shows how the movement’s way of being and temporality persists in Spain following the square occupations, while 15M citizens continue to learn and move forward in less perceptible ways. Democracy Here and Now sheds light on a deeply relational, intersectional, and eco-social mode of democracy, and shows how 15M’s ongoing democratization practices are exemplary of similar grassroots movements around the world, broadening our understandings of what it means to be democratic in the here and now.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 0aDemocratizationzSpainxHistoryy21st century. 0aPolitical participationzSpainxHistoryy21st century. 0aProtest movementszSpainxHistoryy21st century. 0aSocial movementszSpainxHistoryy21st century. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / History & Theory.2bisacsh  a15M.  aCatalan politics.  aSpain.  ademocratization practices.  ajoining hands relationships.  anonviolent contestation.  aparticipatory and representative democracy.  apopulism.  asocial change.1 aTully, James, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTully, James.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022 Englishz978311099451308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Political Science 2022z9783110994407oZDB-23-PLW08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of Toronto Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z978311076715540uhttps://doi.org/10.3138/978148754319840uhttps: